<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[780,1375,2826,3253]" box="[782,1371,2944,2977]" pageId="28" pageNumber="512">Type and paratype were lost in 1945.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[780,1375,2826,3253]" lastBlockId="28.[167,1370,3258,3449]" pageId="28" pageNumber="512">
B. Villa in 1964 described a neotype, but after strong arguments about its validity, A. L. Gardner in 1986 considered it valid. W. D. Webster and J. K. Jones, Jr. in 1980 described a related species, G. 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1367,3141,3174]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="28" pageNumber="512" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
, but it is now considered a subspecies, and brevirostris named by the same authors in 1984 is considered a synonym with 
<taxonomicName box="[665,763,3258,3291]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Glossophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="512" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="morenoi">morenoi</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
